<br>
Here is an example of how it works.<br>
<br>
Old way<br>
You are running from a mob and didn't bother to load up gate, or root or fear or any other defensive spell that might get you out of a jam. Currently we have to stop open spell book. Flip to the page with the spell on it and drag the spell over an already empty slot in hopes that you can mem it before the mob catches you. Most people stop flip to page run until they have enough distance then stop and mem spell. <br>
<br>
New way <br>
While running from mob you can clear current spell icon. Click on empty slot (opens new menu) Select new spell to be memorized and bam! You automaticlly sit and open spell book and spell is dragged to slot. I think this is kind of like a macro function. <br>
<br>
Never used it but I hear it makes things a bit easier for people who have not realized that spell book organization can be a life or death thing. <br>
<br>
Yitamen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xtailia>Xtailia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/2/03 1:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4393.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yeah, if they mess with the ..</span><hr size=1> When I took a look at it when it was first put in there were large chunks of spells missing.  For example, the whole enchanter mez and AoE stun lines were missing, as were many common buffs and debuffs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trelliumtinkerboltz>TrelliumTinkerboltz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/2/03 6:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4393.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yeah, if they mess with the ..</span><hr size=1> Its on the test server. It changes. Some spells were missing, but each minor patch seems to add more spells on the new interface.<br>
<br>
Same goes for the text descriptions for each spell.  Many spells had a missing description at first, but they have been populating the database fairly regularly. Now its rare when I see a missing description.<br>
<br>
I like the new additions.  The spell loads are easier if you know what you want, but you can also still use the old spellbook system just fine. Changing the spell order in your book has no effect on the sort order of the new interface - it is by category and spell level. It is easy to test - make a level 25 character on test and all of your spells are ordered from most powerful to least. But, the new interface is all sorted for you.  Then, if you swap all those spells about in the spell book and move the old ones to page 50, the new interface still retains the same order it had before. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maritzia>Maritzia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Uptight Cleric</span><br>  Posts: 881<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/3/03 9:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4393.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yeah, if they mess with the ..</span><hr size=1> Plus in the new interface the spells are sorted by level and have the level listed, so you don't have to remember which is the higher level spell &lt;grin&gt;, which is something I can never remember.<br>
